PIC SAID HE HAD WX BRIEF. NOTED TSTMS OVR ATLANTIC AND FOG AT ARPT. STATED 
HE WOULD HOLD OVR OCEAN UNTIL ARPT CLR. AIRCRAFT TRACK ON RADAR WAS INTO 
AREA OF TSTMS OVR OCEAN FOLLOWED BY MODE C ALTITUDE DEVIATIONS AND 
LOSS OF RADAR CONTACT. AIRCRAFT RECOVERED FROM OCEAN. EXAMINATION SHOWED 
DOWNWARD BENDING OF STABILIZERS AND TENSION SEPARATION OF BULKHEAD 
WHERE STABILIZERS ATTACH BUT NO IN-FLIGHT SEPARATION OF AIRFRAME.  AIRCRAFT 
WAS MODIFIED WITH BEECH STABILIZER ROOT REINFORCEMENT KIT. 
